    "Management": {
      "text": "Treatment varies by severity of presentation\n[7]\nAirway\nIntubation is needed for altered mental status or seizures\nBreathing\nSupplemental O2\nVentilation\nCirculation\nIVF\nVasopressors for refractory hypotension (\nNorepi\nvs\nphenylephrine\n)\nBB or CCB for tachycardia (Esmolol or Propranolol)\nIf Vtach, initiate code protocol\nBenzodiazepines\nfor agitation\nTreat\nhypokalemia\nif K<3  and\nrhabdo\n(potassium depletion is due to intracellular shift rather than body depletion)\nAntiemetics as needed\nHD\ncan be used in severe cases\nConsult Poison Control",
